# Operational Runbook: Data System Access

## Critical Policy: MCP Only

**Never use CLI tools to query {{MONGODB_NAME}}, {{DATADOG_NAME}}, {{SNOWFLAKE_NAME}}, or other data systems.**

CLI tools bypass the PHI/PII sanitization layer. All data access MUST go through the MCP servers listed below. This applies to all agents, subagents, and tasks.

## MCP Tool Reference

### MongoDB — `mcp__{{MONGODB_MCP_NAME}}__find`, `mcp__{{MONGODB_MCP_NAME}}__aggregate`

Default database: `{{MONGODB_DEFAULT_DB}}` (check your server config).

```
mcp__{{MONGODB_MCP_NAME}}__find:
  collection: "appointments"     # required
  filter: { "org": "..." }       # required — never omit (full scans blocked)
  projection: { "field": 1 }     # always include — limits PHI exposure
  limit: 20                      # always include — default is unbounded
  sort: { "createdAt": -1 }      # optional

mcp__{{MONGODB_MCP_NAME}}__aggregate:
  collection: "appointments"
  pipeline: [{ "$match": {...} }, { "$limit": 20 }]
  # $out and $merge are blocked server-side (read-only)
```

Key collections: `users`, `patients`, `appointments` (add yours here)

### Datadog — `mcp__{{DATADOG_MCP_NAME}}__get_logs`

```
mcp__{{DATADOG_MCP_NAME}}__get_logs:
  query: "service:my-service @rootId:abc123"
  from: "now-1h"     # use narrow ranges — broad queries are expensive
  to: "now"
  limit: 50
```

Hex IDs embedded in log messages may not be found by full-text search. Use attribute filters and filter client-side.

### Snowflake — `mcp__{{SNOWFLAKE_MCP_NAME}}__run_sql`

Read-only (SELECT, DESCRIBE, USE only). Always include LIMIT.

## Setup

1. Build the PHI-safe servers: `./install.sh --extras` (runs `npm install` for each server)
2. Create a launch script for each server (see `mcp-servers/<name>/README.md`)
3. Register in `~/.claude.json` under the `mcpServers` key
4. Customize `phi-config.yaml` for your data model (see `mcp-servers/shared/phi-config.example.yaml`)
